- Thank you.

01:44:44.520 --> 01:44:47.193
- Have you eaten?
- Yes.

01:45:03.000 --> 01:45:07.949
- Are you still annoying your father?
- He slaps my head so hard, Mom!

01:45:08.360 --> 01:45:11.033
I'll end up stupid!

01:45:20.640 --> 01:45:24.189
There's a nice little garden here.
I didn't know.

01:45:24.680 --> 01:45:26.750
It looks in bloom with the snow.

01:45:26.920 --> 01:45:29.309
Mom, is still snowing.

01:45:31.160 --> 01:45:33.879
In a way, you're lucky, Miranda...

01:45:34.040 --> 01:45:37.430
...to be here warm in bed
with this weather.

01:45:38.640 --> 01:45:40.870
He's tired, poor man,
when he gets home.

01:45:41.040 --> 01:45:42.632
- He works all day.
- Yes, Mom.

01:45:42.800 --> 01:45:45.360
You shouldn't answer back.
You're a young man now.

01:45:47.920 --> 01:45:51.469
Don't throw ice! It hurts!

01:45:53.000 --> 01:45:55.070
Take that, Ovo!

01:45:55.240 --> 01:45:58.869
With such wind and such snow,
who's there knocking at my door?

01:45:59.640 --> 01:46:01.756
Idiot! No!

01:46:04.000 --> 01:46:05.956
You stupid!

01:46:06.160 --> 01:46:09.914
- Stop it! No!
- A difficult shot, Your Excellency!

01:46:13.560 --> 01:46:16.597
- Oh, this time I hit you!
- Gradisca!

01:46:17.640 --> 01:46:19.198
Take this, Gradisca!

01:46:19.800 --> 01:46:21.711
No! Not at Gradisca! No!

01:46:22.040 --> 01:46:24.235
You guys are strong!

01:46:24.400 --> 01:46:25.719
Leave Gradisca alone!

01:46:27.000 --> 01:46:28.956
Enough! I give up!

01:46:29.120 --> 01:46:32.237
- Gradisca ran away!
- Gradisca, come here!

01:46:32.400 --> 01:46:36.279
If you break my windows,
I'll kill you all!

01:46:40.480 --> 01:46:41.959
Who is it?

01:46:48.560 --> 01:46:50.312
- What is it?
- I don't know.

01:46:57.800 --> 01:47:00.360
Look, is the couns peacock!

01:47:03.280 --> 01:47:04.838
There! There it is!

01:47:05.200 --> 01:47:06.679
Is coming down!

01:47:14.480 --> 01:47:16.755
Shall we catch it, boys?

01:47:23.360 --> 01:47:24.634
What a moron!

01:47:31.760 --> 01:47:34.797
I don't understand. Whas happened?

01:47:34.960 --> 01:47:37.428
I'll tell you in the car, Uncle.

01:47:37.640 --> 01:47:40.552
Why in the car?
Where are we going?

01:47:40.720 --> 01:47:43.712
Quite near.
To Aunt Zaira's farm.

01:47:43.880 --> 01:47:47.236
A relative's come from America
and wants to say hi to you.

01:47:47.400 --> 01:47:50.995
Well, why doesn't he
come here, then?

01:47:51.160 --> 01:47:53.230
Who is this relative, anyway?

01:48:09.000 --> 01:48:10.274
Hi.

01:48:19.680 --> 01:48:21.477
My aunt is dead.

01:48:27.640 --> 01:48:30.791
Be strong. Be strong.

01:48:34.840 --> 01:48:37.798
Titta, no.

01:48:37.960 --> 01:48:40.713
Don't do that. Titta, open up!

01:48:42.960 --> 01:48:46.111
- Open up.
- No, I won't!

01:49:11.080 --> 01:49:13.196
Lallo! He's fainted.

01:49:13.840 --> 01:49:16.274
Dad, Uncle's feeling sick.

01:49:19.600 --> 01:49:21.431
Take him to the whorehouse then!

01:49:25.960 --> 01:49:28.349
Make the sign of the cross, Dad.

01:49:49.720 --> 01:49:52.029
- How do you feel now?
- Better!

01:49:54.000 --> 01:49:57.879
- Little Miranda!
- Don't take it so hard. Be strong!

01:50:24.600 --> 01:50:27.478
Now, everybody in line.
Where are the orphans?

01:51:33.640 --> 01:51:35.517
Stop that!

01:53:04.760 --> 01:53:07.672
- Hurray for the bride and groom!
- Hurray!

01:53:09.600 --> 01:53:11.716
Give me your arm, Naso.

01:53:11.880 --> 01:53:16.670
Make way, make way,
my breasts are full of milk!

01:53:17.920 --> 01:53:20.354
I raise my glass
to the newlyweds...

01:53:20.520 --> 01:53:23.671
...on this day full of hay
and say, may you live...

01:53:24.320 --> 01:53:26.788
...happily in Battipaglia,
night and day.

01:53:26.960 --> 01:53:30.270
When you're drunk, you can even rhyme!

01:53:33.880 --> 01:53:37.190
Gradisca's getting married
and going away!

01:53:39.640 --> 01:53:42.552
We want to say that we're sorry
if we made you angry...

01:53:42.720 --> 01:53:44.438
...and we hate to see you go!

01:53:46.920 --> 01:53:49.275
We'll miss you badly!

01:53:49.760 --> 01:53:52.593
- Hurray for the newlyweds!
- Hurray!

01:53:53.320 --> 01:53:55.788
Words are silver, silence is gold.

01:53:55.960 --> 01:53:59.191
May this married couple's love
never get old!

01:53:59.360 --> 01:54:01.430
- Where is the bride?
- Over there.

01:54:01.600 --> 01:54:06.549
Our Gradisca is going away because
she's found her Gary Cooper.

01:54:06.720 --> 01:54:09.951
Well, Gary Cooper is a cowboy,
and Matteo is an officer...

01:54:10.120 --> 01:54:13.908
...but love's always love.
Good luck, Gradisca!

01:54:14.760 --> 01:54:16.910
Long live the bride and groom!

01:54:17.080 --> 01:54:20.231
Today you have crowned
your dream of love.

01:54:20.400 --> 01:54:25.076
Now you have a joyous duty
to have many children.

01:54:25.240 --> 01:54:29.199
For your family, for the church
and for your country!

01:54:31.160 --> 01:54:35.756
Now that we're together under this sky,
les drink one more and say goodbye.

01:54:37.920 --> 01:54:40.195
Photograph! Photograph!

01:54:40.360 --> 01:54:42.828
Now we'll take a great photograph!

01:54:43.000 --> 01:54:45.639
- A mirror!
- Everybody get behind the bride!

01:54:45.800 --> 01:54:48.394
This is going to be
a damn good photograph!

01:54:48.560 --> 01:54:52.235
She's lovely, our Ninola!
Why are you crying? Are you crazy?

01:54:52.400 --> 01:54:55.153
- I'm not.
- Get closer together.

01:54:55.320 --> 01:54:57.470
The officer must move back a little.

01:54:57.640 --> 01:54:58.993
Shoo!

01:54:59.160 --> 01:55:00.479
There. In the light.

01:55:01.000 --> 01:55:04.072
- Hold it right there!
- Hey, is raining.

01:55:04.240 --> 01:55:07.471
Big smile. Good, good. Done!

01:55:07.640 --> 01:55:09.437
Another one.

01:55:09.600 --> 01:55:10.828
Excuse me!

01:55:11.000 --> 01:55:13.150
Don't fall all over her, you drunken lout!

01:55:13.320 --> 01:55:15.470
I want to hug her too!

01:55:15.640 --> 01:55:18.837
Is dark over here.
